BBC Proms - David Bowie Tribute (Royal Albert Hall, London, U.K. - 2016-07-29)
Complete Webcast [1280x720]


Live from the Royal Albert Hall Stuart Maconie introduces a celebration and reinterpretation of the music 
of David Bowie with the Berlin-based, 
genre-defying musicians' collective s t a r g a z e and 
its Artistic Director Andre de Ridder.
They are joined by guest singers and 
collaborators - including the Divine Comedy's Neil Hannon, Marc Almond, 
Laura Mvula, Anna Calvi 
and Amanda Palmer - to re-imagine the Bowie catalogue with fresh settings of classic works.
